reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 18, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Exactly what I was looking for, easy 1-person assembly.
reviews.reviewText: I always worked out of the home before the pandemic and got by with a cramped, oddly designed desk left by a previous tenant. It was fine for the few hours a week I used it, but after months working from home I decided to make the jump and set up a working office space. I spent a full day sifting through options and hesitated over this because there are few reviews. I've only just started working on it, but I'm glad I picked this.I wanted a lot of space but wasn't sure I was ready to commit to an L desk, since it limited my placement options. However, it fits perfectly in the corner and it's a bonus that the second arm can be taken off and folded up basically no problem.First off, it took less than fifteen minutes to unpack and assemble. I don't mind putting things together, but if you hate assembly projects, don't have any help, or usually need a hand putting together furniture, this is very easy for one non-technical person to do in just a couple of minutes.Both parts are foldable, which I was ambivalent about, but it does make moving it around easier. It snapped open right away and feels totally sturdy, and screwing the second part on was easy. It's spacious, light in color (which is nice for my dark room), and has plenty of leg room. It looks exactly like in the picture. Came well packed and doesn't wobble at all.I saw some comments about it arriving covered in fiber glass, so I had a wet rag handy. I did find a couple of pieces but I probably wouldn't have noticed if I hadn't read ahead, and it was no problem. The corners are pretty sharp but I prefer the look that way and don't have major concerns with placement, or desk-height kids/pets/etc. As shown, it doesn't come with pre-set holes for cords, but I prefer that and it's easy to position just an inch off the wall (doesn't need to lean on anything to feel stable). I didn't need to tighten anything, and the box arrived with a couple small dings but nothing impacting the desk, which was very well packed (in styrofoam).As long as it holds up, I'm psyched! This seems like it will last just fine, it seems like the finish might be the first thing to go (and if that's all, that's fine as long as it takes a while). If easy assembly is a priority, or you move around a lot and a folding desk is good, definitely consider this. It's just as advertised and a perfectly decent desk, per the other reviews! My cats also love it because there's plenty of room and I don't have to shoo them away to keep them from knocking things over. Glad I bought it!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2021
reviews.reviewText: This was super easy to assemble, especially compared to other desks I've purchased online. Only 3 screws (honestly, I only used 2, bec I didn't see where a 3rd would go, and I didn't read the instructions, but it's really sturdy). I love that the legs simply fold. I bought monitor risers and a little organizing shelf, and my old desk just wasn't wide enough for it all. I found my keyboard was right on the edge, and it wasn't ergonomic, so I bought this one because it's wider but not really expensive. It works great for all my stuff, and I'm much more comfortable working from home now.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 19, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Just something helpful for those who buy this
reviews.reviewText: Overall, I am pleased with the shipping time, price, sturdiness, appearance and how easy the desk is to assemble. There were two very small insignificant (to me) stains on the surface of the desk top. (See photo) They may come out with time and cleaning. Just wanted to give folks a heads up about something. If you have carpet, small children or pets be very careful when unboxing. On the surface of the desktop, there was a solid, light coating of what appears to be fiber glass shards, or overspray from factory sealants. It easily wipes off, but it was all over my shirt front from unboxing and assembly. I was glad my dogs were outside and my son wasn’t over curious before I got cleaned up and wiped the desk down and vacuumed. Overall, very pleased, just thought I would give a friendly ‘heads up’ 😊

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 2, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Couldn't be happier! If I could assemble it with ease ANYONE can.
reviews.reviewText: Easy to assemble to a SHOCKING degree i am terrible at putting even the simplest of things together and yet I was able to do this without frustration. Honestly I was worried that it wasn't going to be supportive or solid enough because of how easy it was to assemble...well let's just say I was wrong. This was precisely what I needed and I spent literally months looking at different desks till I finally pulled the trigger on this one and I couldn't be happier! During COVID times the need for a solid, sturdy, beautiful, functional and easy to assemble home office desk is higher than ever...well look no further!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 3, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars best desk for its price
reviews.reviewText: i got this desk for about $160 and it's perfect. i live in a room with another roommate but it still fits! i put it on the edge of my bed so i have a nice corner to myself and it's very roomy. The desk has one side that is wider than the other which i really love. i do most of my work on the wider side of the desk and keep important paper/documents on the other side. it's soooooo easy to set up. it's a folding table! just open up the legs and tada it's done! if you ever don't want to use the narrower side of the desk you can just take it off and just use the wider side. not every L shape table can do that and this one is one of a kind. i love it so much.
